"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76651","Attorney General","false","2014-09-01","<p> </p><p>Tables showing the information requested for the Crown Prosecution Service and the Serious Fraud Office have been placed in the Library of the House.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The remaining Law Officers’ Departments are unable to provide any reliable estimates of the amount spent annually on contracted out services since 2009-10 without incurring a disproportionate cost.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2014-09-01T14:56:03.9993549Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76651/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76651/answer","Tables for deposit- PQ 204893  contracted work in LOD's.doc","Tables for deposit- PQ 204893  contracted work in LOD's.doc","Table - contracted out services - LOD's","Table - contracted out services - LOD's","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76651/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2014-07-09","Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, how much and what proportion of the Law Officers' Departments' budget was spent on activities which were contracted out in (a) 2009-10, (b) 2010-11, (c) 2011-12, (d) 2012-13 and (e) 2013-14; and how much and what proportion of the Law Officers' Department's budget he expects to be contracted out in 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","204893"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76652","Attorney General","false","2014-07-14","<p>The Law Officers have the use of one day and one evening car provided by the Government Car Service. The Attorney General's Office do not keep a record of the number of car journeys undertaken by the Law Officers, or of the number of journeys made specifically for transporting a red box.</p><p> </p>","North East Hertfordshire","Oliver Heald",,"2014-07-14T16:36:20.7173902Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76652/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76652/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76652/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2014-07-09","Ministers: Official Cars","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, how many journeys Ministers of the Law Officers' Departments have made using the Government Car Service; and how many such journeys were for the transportation of a red box.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","204931"
