"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76655","HM Treasury","false","2014-07-16","<p>The Money Advice Service (MAS) is an independent non-governmental public body set up with a statutory objective to raise public understanding and knowledge of financial matters and the ability of people to manage their own financial affairs.</p><p>The Government is not aware that MAS has any imminent plans to launch a price comparison website for short term loans.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2014-07-16T16:38:09.9861717Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76655/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76655/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76655/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-07-09","Money Advice Service","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what progress the Money Advice Service has made on launching a price comparison website for short term loans.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","204984"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76656","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-07-17","<p>We do not hold any figures by region, only for UK as a whole.</p><p>UK defence and security exports in 2013 totalled £13 billion, which represents a 13% increase on the previous year.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-07-17T16:24:32.133Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76656/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76656/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76656/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-07-09","Arms Trade: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what the value of Northern Ireland's defence and security exports was in 2013.","false","Biography information for Mr Ivan Lewis","Bury South","Mr Ivan Lewis","204824"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76657","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-07-15","<p>This Department contributes to the EU guidance for corrective action, including product recalls. This guidance provides best practice for any specific case where corrective action is required, including exceptional cases where a recall is justified. The guidance was last revised in 2011. BIS officials continue to work with interested parties, including other EU Member States, trade associations, such as AMDEA, and others such Electrical Safety First to consider options for improving the overall effectiveness of product recalls, including what, if any, additional guidance should be provided.</p>","East Dunbartonshire","Jo Swinson",,"2014-07-15T14:35:59.43626Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76657/answer","Biography information for Jo Swinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76657/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76657/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-07-09","Electrical Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will review the guidance his Department issues on electrical appliance recalls to reflect the consequences of recent high-profile recall actions.","false","Biography information for Ann McKechin","Glasgow North","Ann McKechin","204837"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76658","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-07-15","<p>A comprehensive answer cannot be provided without incurring disproportionate cost as the Department does not maintain a single register of all contracted out services. However, the Department does routinely publish details of the ‘Outsourced Programme Managed Services' in its annual resource accounts. These are contracts the Department has placed to manage the delivery of programmes and work to support the Department's objectives.</p><p>The figures over the financial years in question along with the total programme expenditure for the core Department are as follows:</p><p><strong>F/Yr OutsourcedService Costs Total Programme Expenditure</strong></p><p>2013/14 £23.0m £23,566m</p><p>2012/13 £34.9m £21,077m</p><p>2011/12 £10.2m £22,373m</p><p>2010/11 £29.9m £25,734m</p><p>2009/10 £69.2m £24,610m</p><p><strong>Note:</strong> the total programme expenditure reflects non-administration costs, including payment of grant-in-aid, grants and other disbursements in support of policy initiatives.</p>","East Dunbartonshire","Jo Swinson",,"2014-07-15T15:45:15.1241987Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76658/answer","Biography information for Jo Swinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76658/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76658/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-07-09","Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how much and what proportion of his Department's budget was spent on activities which were contracted out in (a) 2009-10, (b) 2010-11, (c) 2011-12, (d) 2012-13 and (e) 2013-14; and how much and what proportion of his Department's budget he expects to be contracted out in 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","204892"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76659","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-16","<p>Data on the number of claims made by appellants with a terminal condition on the grounds of unfair dismissal is not collated centrally by HM Courts &amp; Tribunals Service (HMCTS). This information could only be provided at a disproportionate cost by manually checking hard copy tribunal files or judgments.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2014-07-16T10:41:59.326546Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76659/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76659/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76659/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-09","Terminal Illnesses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many employment tribunals in which the appellant had a terminal condition and was contesting a dismissal that occurred because of their diagnosis took place in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Liz Kendall","Leicester West","Liz Kendall","204907"
