"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76662","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-07-16","<p>The Department does not keep records of how much money has been or will be spent in individual constituencies. To provide an answer for a particular area would require significant analysis and incur disproportionate cost.</p>","East Dunbartonshire","Jo Swinson",,"2014-07-16T14:03:21.1294667Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76662/answer","Biography information for Jo Swinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76662/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76662/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-07-09","Morecambe","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will estimate how much money his Department has spent in Morecambe and Lunesdale constituency since May 2010.","false","Biography information for David Morris","Morecambe and Lunesdale","David Morris","204769"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76663","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-07-17","<p>A Regulatory Impact Assessment relating to the provision of Local Land Charges has been produced by Land Registry and approved by BIS and the Regulatory Policy Committee.</p><p><a href="http://www.landregistry.gov.uk/__data/assets/pdf_file/0007/91627/LR_Impact-Assessment_Wider-Powers-and-LLC-Consultation_FINAL.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.landregistry.gov.uk/__data/assets/pdf_file/0007/91627/LR_Impact-Assessment_Wider-Powers-and-LLC-Consultation_FINAL.pdf</a></p><p>This takes into account the potential benefits of a fully digitised service with improved turnaround times, greater efficiencies and a lower fee for the customer. The Impact Assessment states that creating a single, digital Local Land Charges register will result in the significant majority of customers, including businesses, paying a lower fee per purchase for a faster service.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-07-17T16:26:26.5853577Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76663/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76663/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76663/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-07-09","Property Searches","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment he has made of the effect of centralising local land charges registers on small and medium-sized enterprises and micro-businesses currently providing such services as local land charges searches.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","204724"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76664","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-07-22","<p>Land Registry officials have engaged bodies that represent a range of small and medium-sized enterprises and micro-businesses throughout the research into Local Land Charges, during the year-long prototype in 2012-13. These bodies include; the Council of Personal Search Organisations, which is a trade organisation, the Association of Independent Personal Search Agents, together with a number of personal search companies. This engagement will continue throughout the development of the policy.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-07-22T14:24:42.4595362Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76664/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76664/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76664/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-07-09","Property Searches","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what recent discussions he has had with representatives of small and medium-sized enterprises and micro-businesses currently providing local land charges searches.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","204725"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76665","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-07-17","<p>Land Registry undertook a full public consultation on Local Land Charges and Wider Powers between 16 January 2014 and 9 March 2014. This consultation received 627 responses and the Government published its response on 16 June 2014.</p><p><a href="http://www.landregistry.gov.uk/__data/assets/pdf_file/0006/91626/Govt-Response_Report-on-Wider-Powers-LLC-Consultation-16-6-14.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.landregistry.gov.uk/__data/assets/pdf_file/0006/91626/Govt-Response_Report-on-Wider-Powers-LLC-Consultation-16-6-14.pdf</a></p><p>This response highlights all of the representations made by respondents. Land Registry has engaged extensively with stakeholders throughout its research into Local Land Charges and this engagement is ongoing.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-07-17T16:30:40.390582Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76665/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76665/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76665/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-07-09","Property Searches","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what representations he has received on the effect of changes to be made in the Infrastructure Bill [Lords] on improving completion times for LLC1 local searches.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","204750"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76666","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-07-17","<p>Creating a single, digital Local Land Charges register will lead to a reduction in search turnaround times on average. Searches currently take between 1 and more than 20 days and Land Registry intends to reduce this to minutes. In 2013/14, Land Registry dealt with 11.5 million requests for registers of title and title plans, of which 98.2% were delivered electronically to the customer: Local Land Charges searches are similar and Land Registry will utilise its expertise to provide them in a similar way.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-07-17T16:28:23.053512Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76666/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76666/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76666/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-07-09","Property Searches","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment he has made of the effect on completion times for LLC1 local searches as a result of centralising the local land charges register in line with proposals in the Infrastructure Bill [Lords].","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","204751"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76667","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-22","<p>I refer my honourable friend to the answer I gave to his written question (205872) on 21 July 2014 (Hansard reference: 21 July 2014 Column 854W).</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-07-22T16:36:21.5194198Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76667/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76667/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76667/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-09","Cybercrime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will bring forward legislative proposals to ensure that online theft is punishable in line with traditional theft of items of the same monetary value.","false","Biography information for Mike Weatherley","Hove","Mike Weatherley","204684"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76668","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-07-15","<p> </p><p>The results of the initial phase of the Human Brain Project (HBP) will provide more detail on how it will address its objectives. The UK Research Councils, the Biotechnology and Biological Sciences Research Council (BBSRC), the Engineering and Physical Sciences Research Council (EPSRC) and the Medical Research Council (MRC) will hold discussions with UK researchers at that point to decide on any future involvement.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The UK makes no current financial contribution to the HBP. However, the project includes the expertise of some key UK researchers and is making use of the hardware platform, SpiNNaker, which was previously developed with £2.7 million of support from the EPSRC.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Havant","Mr David Willetts","204686","2014-07-15T12:15:32.5333427Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76668/answer","Biography information for Lord Willetts","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76668/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76668/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-07-09","Brain: Research","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what recent assessment he has made of the work of the Human Brain project; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Graham Stringer","Blackley and Broughton","Graham Stringer","204685"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76669","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-07-15","<p> </p><p>The results of the initial phase of the Human Brain Project (HBP) will provide more detail on how it will address its objectives. The UK Research Councils, the Biotechnology and Biological Sciences Research Council (BBSRC), the Engineering and Physical Sciences Research Council (EPSRC) and the Medical Research Council (MRC) will hold discussions with UK researchers at that point to decide on any future involvement.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The UK makes no current financial contribution to the HBP. However, the project includes the expertise of some key UK researchers and is making use of the hardware platform, SpiNNaker, which was previously developed with £2.7 million of support from the EPSRC.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Havant","Mr David Willetts","204685","2014-07-15T12:15:32.6035428Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76669/answer","Biography information for Lord Willetts","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76669/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76669/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-07-09","Brain: Research","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what the UK's financial contribution to the Human Brain project is in addition to the contribution of the EU Commission.","false","Biography information for Graham Stringer","Blackley and Broughton","Graham Stringer","204686"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76670","Cabinet Office","false","2014-07-16","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer my Rt Hon. Friend the Member for Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner gave to the hon. Member for Barnsley East on 10 July 2014 (Official Report) Column Ref: 361W.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude",,"2014-07-16T16:50:38.0538268Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76670/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76670/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76670/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-07-09","Electronic Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what assessment he has made of the number of copycat websites which charge fees for free Government services.","false","Biography information for Cathy Jamieson","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Cathy Jamieson","204723"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76671","Cabinet Office","false","2014-07-16","<p>The Deputy Prime Minister's Office and the Office of the Leader of the House of Commons are integral parts of the Cabinet Office and are included in this reply.</p><p>Information about payroll costs and non-consolidated pay awards in the Cabinet Office are available at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/payroll-costs-and-non-consolidated-pay-data" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/payroll-costs-and-non-consolidated-pay-data</a> . Further information about pay costs is also available in the Cabinet Office Annual Report and Accounts and are available at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/cabinet-office-annual-reports-and-accounts" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/cabinet-office-annual-reports-and-accounts#</a> .</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude","204767","2014-07-16T16:30:26.5689799Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76671/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76671/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76671/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-07-09","Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many officials in his Department, of each grade, have remained at that grade since 2010 but received a pay rise; and how much of a rise each such person at each such grade has received.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Bradshaw","Exeter","Mr Ben Bradshaw","204762"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76672","Cabinet Office","false","2014-07-14","<p>As was the situation under previous Administrations, the Cabinet Office accounts do not break down expenditure by constituency.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude",,"2014-07-14T12:06:43.9800387Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76672/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76672/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76672/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-07-09","Morecambe","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, if he will estimate how much money his Department has spent in Morecambe and Lunesdale constituency since May 2010.","false","Biography information for David Morris","Morecambe and Lunesdale","David Morris","204770"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76673","Department of Health","false","2014-07-16","<p>Data on the number of people diagnosed with a terminal illness is not collected centrally.</p><p> </p><p>Information recorded in Electronic Palliative Care Co-ordination Systems (EPaCCs), also known as ‘locality registers' or ‘end of life care registers' is not collected centrally. EPaCCs are implemented locally and are the responsibility of local commissioners. The core data set for EPaCCs does not include information about a dying person's employment status.</p><p> </p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","204905","2014-07-16T12:54:47.1277153Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76673/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76673/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76673/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-09","Terminal Illnesses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many working-age people in England were diagnosed with a terminal illness in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Liz Kendall","Leicester West","Liz Kendall","204906"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76674","Cabinet Office","false","2014-07-16","<p>The Cabinet Office has no central record of any dismissals from the department on incapacity grounds following diagnosis of a terminal health condition in the last five years.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude",,"2014-07-16T16:03:08.049794Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76674/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76674/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76674/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-07-09","Terminal Illnesses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many people were dismissed from employment on incapacity grounds following diagnosis of a terminal health condition in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Liz Kendall","Leicester West","Liz Kendall","204904"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76675","Cabinet Office","false","2014-07-14","<p>Expenditure incurred by other Government departments is not held by the Cabinet Office.</p><p>Spend incurred by my department on the items requested can only be obtained at disproportionate cost. However, my department has not spent money on World Cup Tickets.</p><p>This Government reduced the percentage of the Cabinet Office annual pay bill spent on in year rewards from 0.55%, prior to May 2010, to 0.25% now.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude","204900 ; 204901 ; 204902 ; 204903","2014-07-14T16:13:55.3419538Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76675/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76675/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76675/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-07-09","Football: World Cup","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how much each Government department spent on tickets to the World Cup 2014; and for what purposes those tickets were acquired.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","204899"
