"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76722","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-07-14","<p>The Government recognises the important role that the Portable Antiquities Scheme plays in furthering our understanding of British history and archaeology. The resource allocations given to the British Museum up to 2015-16 include funding for its administration of the Portable Antiquities Scheme. Future funding arrangements will be considered as part of the next spending review.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2014-07-14T11:12:00.6468192Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76722/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76722/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76722/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-07-09","Portable Antiquities Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what his future funding plans are for the Portable Antiquities scheme; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","204871"
