"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76822","Department of Health","false","2014-07-14","<p>At the 2013-14 financial year-end, there were 102 National Health Service trusts and 147 foundation trusts, each of which produced their own financial accounts. Of which, the Department recognise 62 non-specialist acute NHS trusts and 83 non-specialist foundation trusts, 145 organisations in total.</p><p> </p><p>Of these 145 organisations, the majority (ie 87) reported a financial surplus whilst 58 reported a financial deficit.</p><p> </p><p>NHS providers are required to deliver a break-even position. Where deficits occur they must be tackled in the right way. The NHS Trust Development Authority and Monitor, the independent regulator for foundation trusts, have a robust process for ensuring that trusts in deficit put a plan in place to recover their position, which in some instances will only be achieved in the medium term.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-07-14T16:34:54.2757979Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76822/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76822/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76822/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-09","Hospitals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many non-specialist trust acute hospitals were in financial deficit at the end of the 2013-14 financial year.","false","Biography information for Derek Twigg","Halton","Derek Twigg","204958"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76823","Department of Health","false","2014-07-16","<p>The latest annual workforce census data, published by the Health and Social Care Information Centre, provides information on the numbers of radiographers and radiologists working in the National Health Service in England as at 30 September each year. The numbers of full time equivalent radiographers and radiologists working in the NHS in England in each of the last five years are shown in the attached table. The latest available statistics are as at 30 September 2013 and were published on 25 March 2014.</p><p> </p><p>Radiographers and radiologists also work in the private and independent sectors but the numbers are not collected centrally. The Society of Radiographers may be able to supply more information on radiographers. Their website is available at:</p><p> </p><p>www.sor.org/</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-07-16T14:01:04.0299821Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76823/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76823/answer","PQ204908_-_Radiography staff table[1].docx","PQ204908_-_Radiography staff table[1].docx","Radiography staff in England","Radiography staff in England","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76823/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-09","Radiology","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many (a) radiographers and (b) radiologists were in practice in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Baroness McIntosh of Pickering","Thirsk and Malton","Miss Anne McIntosh","204908"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76824","Department of Health","false","2014-07-16","<p>The Innovation, Health and Wealth programme is a 10-year strategy, launched in December 2011, alongside the Government's Strategy for the UK Life Sciences.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has advised that considerable progress has already been made, with the vast majority of actions now complete and showing positive early signs of improvement in uptake and utility of new medicines and technologies in the National Health Service. NHS England, along with key stakeholders from the NHS, industry and representative bodies, has recently completed a refresh of the programme. This reviewed progress to date and identified areas where further action is needed. NHS England plans to publish the results of that review later this year.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has advised that information on expenditure on the Innovation, Health and Wealth programme is not available. Funding for the programme is shown in the table:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Innovation Health and Wealth programme</p></td><td><p>2013-14</p><p>budget</p><p>£000</p></td><td><p>2014-15</p><p>budget</p><p>£000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Academic Health Science Networks (AHSNs)</p></td><td><p>56,400</p></td><td><p>53,600</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Innovation scorecard</p></td><td><p>100</p></td><td><p>100</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Healthcare UK</p></td><td><p>1,000</p></td><td><p>615</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Innovation challenge prizes</p></td><td><p>1,100</p></td><td><p>676</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Regional Innovation Fund</p></td><td><p>5,000</p></td><td><p>3,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Small Business Research Initiative(through AHSNs)</p></td><td><p>10,000</p></td><td><p>20,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>NICE Implementation Collaborative</p></td><td><p>5</p></td><td><p>15</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Industry council</p></td><td><p>5</p></td><td><p>15</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Exchange</p></td><td><p>50</p></td><td><p>60</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>EXPO</p></td><td><p>53</p></td><td><p>50</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Exchange communications</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>50</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Fellowship</p></td><td><p>100</p></td><td><p>50</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Patient pull</p></td><td><p>20</p><p>(not spent)</p></td><td><p>20</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Wheelchair tariff</p></td><td><p>167</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><em>Source</em>: Information provided by NHS England</p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-07-16T13:04:04.0341368Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76824/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76824/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76824/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-09","NHS: Innovation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the performance of the Innovation, Health and Wealth programme; and what the costs of the programme to date have been in respect of (a) the NHS and (b) external consultancies.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","204839"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76825","Department of Health","false","2014-07-16","<p>The Department has made no recent assessment of the effect of this framework and guidance on the management of intellectual property in the National Health Service.</p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-07-16T13:52:48.9357725Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76825/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76825/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76825/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-09","NHS: Innovation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, with reference to his Department's publication, The NHS as an Innovative Organisation: A Framework and Guidance on the Management of Intellectual Property in the NHS, published in 2002, which of the conclusions of that report have been adopted; and what assessment he has made of the effect on the NHS of their adoption.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","204840"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76826","Department of Health","false","2014-07-14","<p>We currently have no plans to do so.</p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter","204249","2014-07-14T13:43:40.3460995Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76826/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76826/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76826/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-09","NHS: Innovation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 18 June 2014, Official Report, column 617W, on the NHS, if he will ensure that his Department's proposals arising from the Innovation, Health and Wealth review of NHS intellectual property that was completed in Autumn 2012 will be published before the summer recess.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","204841"
