"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76829","Department of Health","false","2014-07-16","<p>No assessment has been made of the implications for the National Health Service of the decision by the General Dental Council (GDC) on their proposal to increase the annual retention fee.</p><p> </p><p>The GDC is an independent body and it is therefore for the GDC Council to determine the level of the annual fee it charges for registration. The proposed fee increase is subject to public consultation where the GDC's case will be scrutinised. The Department does not usually contribute to such consultations but all professional regulators, including the GDC, are aware of the Department's position on registration fees. In February 2011, the Government published Enabling Excellence, which states that we would not expect registration fees to increase beyond their current levels, unless there is a clear and robust business case that any increase is essential to ensure the exercise of statutory duties.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-07-16T13:25:08.1119783Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76829/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76829/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76829/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-09","General Dental Council","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the implications for the NHS of the decision by the General Dental Council to raise their compulsory statutory annual retention fee from £576 per annum to £945 per annum.","false","Biography information for Mr David Anderson","Blaydon","Mr David Anderson","204838"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76830","Department of Health","false","2014-07-14","<p>The information requested is shown in the attached table.</p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-07-14T15:19:49.89","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76830/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76830/answer","PQ204865 - Table.xlsx","PQ204865 - Table.xlsx","Table","Table","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76830/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-09","General Practitioners: Warrington","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many full-time equivalent GPs were working in Warrington in each year since 2007-08.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","204865"
