"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76832","Cabinet Office","false","2014-07-14","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2014-07-14T13:26:16.733","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76832/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76832/answer","PQ204962.xlsx ; PQ204962.pdf","PQ204962.xlsx ; PQ204962.pdf","Excel Sheet - Cancer Deaths ; ONS Letter to Member","Excel Sheet - Cancer Deaths ; ONS Letter to Member","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76832/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-07-09","Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many early deaths from cancer have occurred among (a) men and (b) women in each local authority area in each year since 2001; and what proportion of those diagnosed with cancer such deaths represented.","false","Biography information for Derek Twigg","Halton","Derek Twigg","204962"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76833","Department of Health","false","2014-07-14","<p>Lead is a known neurotoxicant and has been shown to affect cognitive function, especially following exposure during early life. However, the causes of dementia are multifactorial and it would be very difficult to investigate whether exposure to lead in childhood leads to early onset of dementia.</p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb",,"2014-07-14T12:42:44.6266324Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76833/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76833/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76833/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-09","Dementia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of whether childhood exposure to lead can lead to the early onset of dementia.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","204967"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76834","Home Office","false","2014-07-22","<p> </p><p> </p><p>For 1 April 2013 to 31 March 2014, UK Visas and Immigration replied to <br>correspondence from hon. Members within an average of 26 days. Information on <br>the average time taken to reply to urgent visa cases is not recorded centrally <br>and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-07-22T10:21:10.9022358Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76834/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76834/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76834/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76834/answer/previousversion/9733","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-09","UK Visas and Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the average time taken for the Director General, UK Visas and Immigration to reply to hon. Members in (a) all and (b) urgent visit visa cases was in the last 12 months; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mike Gapes","Ilford South","Mike Gapes","204979"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76835","Home Office","false","2014-07-21","<p> </p><p> </p><p>Guidance is available to all staff involved in responding to correspondence from hon. Members. This guidance explains when it is appropriate for staff to contact the business unit dealing with the case. <br><br>Additionally, the Home Office have issued an Information Fact Sheet – ‘Family Visit Visa Information Fact Sheet for Members of Parliament acting on behalf of their constituents’ to hon. Members. The Information Fact Sheet is available on the Home Office MP website.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-07-21T16:57:32.9828503Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76835/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76835/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76835/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76835/answer/previousversion/9728","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-09","UK Visas and Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what guidance she has issued to UK Visas and Immigration Directorate on responding to hon. Members' representations on visit visa cases.","false","Biography information for Mike Gapes","Ilford South","Mike Gapes","204977"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76836","Home Office","false","2014-07-21","<p> </p><p> </p><p>A Home Office official responded to the hon. Member on 10 July 2014.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-07-21T16:29:21.9576022Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76836/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76836/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76836/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76836/answer/previousversion/9730","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-09","UK Visas and Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when the hon. Member for Ilford South will receive a reply from the Director General, UK Visas and Immigration to the urgent representations he made on behalf of his constituents Mr and Mrs Mehta on 16 June 2014; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mike Gapes","Ilford South","Mike Gapes","204976"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76837","Home Office","false","2014-07-14","<p> </p><p>The information cannot be provided without incurring disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-07-14T13:20:12.4913229Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76837/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76837/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76837/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-09","Ministers: Official Cars","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many journeys Ministers of her Department have made using the Government Car Service; and how many such journeys were for the transportation of a red box.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","204940"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76838","Home Office","false","2014-07-22","<p> </p><p> </p><p>The Coalition Government’s Ending Gang and Youth Violence programme is the <br>first such programme to tackle the issue of gang-affected women and girls. <br><br>Women and girls who come into contact with street gangs are at greater risk of <br>violence, particularly sexual violence. The Home Office has provided £1.2 <br>million funding for 13 Young People’s Advocates over three years (April 2012 – <br>March 2015). The Advocates provide direct support to young women who have been <br>victims, or are at risk of, sexual violence by gangs.<br><br>Action to protect girls from becoming involved in gang-related crime is set out <br>in the ‘Ending Gang and Youth Violence: One Year On’ (November 2012) and <br>‘Ending Gang and Youth Violence Annual Report 2013’ (December 2013) documents.<br><br>The reports are available on the GOV.UK website.<br><br>In addition, I have undertaken targeted visits to identify good practice on the <br>ground.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Lewes","Norman Baker",,"2014-07-22T10:20:30.7834313Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76838/answer","Biography information for Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76838/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76838/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-09","Crimes of Violence: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps the Government is taking to tackle gender-based violence in gangs (a) generally and (b) in respect of sexual violence against girls and young women; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dr Hywel Francis","Aberavon","Dr Hywel Francis","204922"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76839","Home Office","false","2014-07-17","<p> </p><p>The work of the UK Border Agency is now undertaken by the UK Visas and <br>Immigration, Border Force and Immigration Enforcement Directorates of the Home <br>Department. For border security reasons, it is not possible to provide a <br>breakdown of staff numbers by location. Furthermore, staff are deployed <br>flexibly according to demand and therefore move between locations. As at 31st <br>May 2014, however, there were 164 members of staff based in Northern Ireland <br>across the UK Visas and Immigration, Border Force and Immigration Enforcement <br>Directorates.</p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-07-17T14:09:12.2303339Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76839/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76839/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76839/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-09","UK Border Agency: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many UK Border Agency staff are based at (a) its Belfast public enquiry office, (b) Belfast City Airport, (c) Belfast International Airport, (d) City of Derry Airport and (e) ports and harbours in Northern Ireland; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","204924"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76840","Home Office","false","2014-07-21","<p> </p><p>Officials within UK Visas and Immigration review all representations to the Director General and where appropriate they will liaise with the overseas post to request a review of the decision. The case that the Hon. Member recently raised has been referred to post for review.</p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-07-21T16:26:32.7027059Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76840/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76840/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76840/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76840/answer/previousversion/9731","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-09","UK Visas and Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, for what reasons hon. Members' recent representations to the Director General, UK Visas and Immigration were not referred to the post for a review; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mike Gapes","Ilford South","Mike Gapes","204978"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76841","Home Office","false","2014-07-17","<p> </p><p>The work of the UK Border Agency is now undertaken by the UK Visas and <br>Immigration, Border Force and Immigration Enforcement Directorates of the Home <br>Department<br><br>The Home Office does not centrally hold data on locations that staff are <br>recruited from. To identify this information, we would therefore need to review <br>each individual recruitment campaign, which would incur disproportionate cost. <br><br>Staff are deployed flexibly according to demand and move between locations and <br>regions. In order to provide information therefore on staff in the UK Visas and <br>Immigration, Border Force and Immigration Enforcement Directorates who reside <br>in Northern Ireland, locally held deployment plans would need <br>to be collected and analysed against individual employee's home addresses. This <br>would incur disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-07-17T14:10:40.2479108Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76841/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76841/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76841/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-09","UK Border Agency: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many UK Border Agency staff employed in Northern Ireland (a) are recruited locally and (b) reside in Northern Ireland; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","204925"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76842","Home Office","false","2014-07-25","<p>On 7 July the Home Secretary announced an independent inquiry into child sexual abuse. The inquiry will consider whether public bodies – and other non-state institutions – have taken seriously their duty of care to protect children from sexual abuse. The Inquiry will co-operate fully with Devolved Administrations. However all relevant issues in Scotland and Northern Ireland are now devolved and will be a matter for those administrations to consider. In Wales the inquiry will cover those institutions which concern non-devolved matters. The Home Secretary has made clear that the Home Office will talk to the Devolved Administrations and work with them on this Inquiry.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Lewes","Norman Baker",,"2014-07-25T13:32:20.6106563Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76842/answer","Biography information for Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76842/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76842/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-09","Children: Abuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether the Butler-Sloss Inquiry into child abuse will have scope to include public bodies and non-state institutions based in Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Mr Ivan Lewis","Bury South","Mr Ivan Lewis","204875"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76843","Home Office","false","2014-07-25","<p>On 7 July the Home Secretary announced an independent inquiry into child sexual abuse. The inquiry will consider whether public bodies – and other non-state institutions – have taken seriously their duty of care to protect children from sexual abuse. The Inquiry will co-operate fully with Devolved Administrations. However all relevant issues in Scotland and Northern Ireland are now devolved and will be a matter for those administrations to consider. In Wales the inquiry will cover those institutions which concern non-devolved matters. The Home Secretary has made clear that the Home Office will talk to the Devolved Administrations and work with them on this Inquiry.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Lewes","Norman Baker",,"2014-07-25T13:31:27.6776508Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76843/answer","Biography information for Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76843/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76843/answer","Lewes","Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76843/answer/previousversion/9747","Biography information for Norman Baker","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-09","Kincora Children's Home","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will include Kincora Boys Home in East Belfast in the scope of the Butler-Sloss child abuse inquiry.","false","Biography information for Naomi Long","Belfast East","Naomi Long","204811"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76844","Home Office","false","2014-07-17","<p> </p><p>Her Majesty's Passport Office does not collect performance data at this level. <br>Performance is monitored at a national level as HMPO distributes work across <br>the UK estate to manage variation in local levels of passport demand. The cost <br>of identifying the information in the format requested would be <br>disproportionate.</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-07-17T13:58:22.5817116Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76844/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76844/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76844/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76844/answer/previousversion/9746","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-09","Passports: Warrington","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many passport renewals for people in (a) Warrington Borough and (b) Warrington North constituency were completed within three weeks of receipt in each year since 2009 and in 2014 to date.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","204790"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76845","Home Office","false","2014-07-17","<p> </p><p>The Home Office's financial system does not record how much is spent by <br>constituency and therefore we are unable to answer the question.</p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-07-17T14:09:49.565499Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76845/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76845/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76845/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-09","Morecambe","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will estimate how much money her Department has spent in Morecambe and Lunesdale constituency since May 2010.","false","Biography information for David Morris","Morecambe and Lunesdale","David Morris","204778"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76846","Home Office","false","2014-07-25","<p>On 7 July the Home Secretary announced an independent inquiry into child sexual abuse. The inquiry will consider whether public bodies - and other non-state institutions-have taken seriously their duty of care to protect children from sexual abuse. The Inquiry will co-operate fully with Devolved Administrations. However all relevant issues in Scotland and Northern Ireland are now devolved and will be a matter for those administrations to consider. In Wales the inquiry will cover those institutions which concern non-devolved matters. The Home Secretary has made clear that the Home Office will talk to the Devolved Administrations and work with them on this Inquiry.</p><p> </p>","Lewes","Norman Baker",,"2014-07-25T13:30:32.2518064Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76846/answer","Biography information for Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76846/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76846/answer","Lewes","Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76846/answer/previousversion/9743","Biography information for Norman Baker","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-09","Children: Abuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what discussions she had with the Scottish Government on the Butler-Sloss inquiry into child abuse.","false","Biography information for Cathy Jamieson","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Cathy Jamieson","204699"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76847","Home Office","false","2014-07-21","<p> </p><p> </p><p>Border Force has a duty under section 55 of the Borders, Citizenship and <br>Immigration Act 2009 to safeguard and promote the welfare of children. All <br>Border Force officers undergo mandatory training and have guidance to enable <br>them to fulfil this important duty in an appropriate manner. Checks are <br>conducted on passengers arriving in the UK in accordance with the Border Force <br>Operating Mandate. <br><br>Where a child is encountered at the border, and it is not immediately apparent <br>that the accompanying adult is their parent or guardian, Border Force officers <br>will ask questions to satisfy themselves as to the child’s welfare and to <br>discharge their statutory duty. This will be done as quickly and as sensitively <br>as possible to avoid unnecessary delay and distress to the passenger and their <br>accompanying family.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-07-21T14:52:16.9104901Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76847/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76847/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76847/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76847/answer/previousversion/9737","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-09","Immigration Controls","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will take steps to ensure that staff of her Department alleviate distress suffered by families who are subject to questioning at border control because the children have different surnames to their parents.","false","Biography information for Sheila Gilmore","Edinburgh East","Sheila Gilmore","204701"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76848","Home Office","false","2014-07-17","<p> </p><p>There are no plans to use the passport to identify parental relationships as <br>this would change the fundamental purpose of the document which is for <br>travel. Guidance on children travelling to the UK, including children <br>travelling with a parent who may have a different family name to the child, can <br>be found at: <br>https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/children-travelling-to-the-uk</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-07-17T14:04:57.8728559Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76848/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76848/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76848/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76848/answer/previousversion/9740","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-09","Passports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will make it her policy that appropriate information about parents is included on children's passports and collected to reduce difficulties at border control for children whose surnames differ from their parents' surnames.","false","Biography information for Sheila Gilmore","Edinburgh East","Sheila Gilmore","204704"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76849","Home Office","false","2014-07-17","<p> </p><p>There are no plans to use the passport to identify parental relationships as <br>this would change the fundamental purpose of the document which is for <br>travel. Guidance on children travelling to the UK, including children <br>travelling with a parent who may have a different family name to the child, can <br>be found at: <br>https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/children-travelling-to-the-uk</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-07-17T14:04:26.1227535Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76849/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76849/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76849/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76849/answer/previousversion/9739","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-09","Passports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if her Department will amend the official observations section of children's passports to allow a note when a holder's parent has a different surname to that of the child.","false","Biography information for Sheila Gilmore","Edinburgh East","Sheila Gilmore","204702"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76850","Home Office","false","2014-07-17","<p> </p><p>The Government works closely with the police to support the policing of illegal <br>cannabis cultivation. The police response to tackle commercial cannabis <br>cultivation includes proactive operations to identify and close down these <br>farms and disrupt the organised crime groups behind them. The police also work <br>to improve their knowledge and understanding of the trade through activity-led <br>intelligence gathering.<br><br>Cannabis farms are often established by organised crime groups in residential <br>properties, bringing criminality into communities. The Government is therefore <br>also working with other partners with an interest in this area, such as energy <br>companies and the property sector, to promote co-operation and the sharing of <br>best practice in tackling cannabis farms. <br><br>We have also worked in partnership with Crimestoppers on a ‘scratch and sniff' <br>cannabis card campaign, which I launched on 26 June and which will run for <br>three months. This involves distributing ‘scratch and sniff' cards to the public to <br>inform them about the signs to spot and the specific smell of cannabis when it <br>is growing. Hot spot areas, as informed by police intelligence, have been <br>targeted by police forces throughout the UK. A similar campaign last year led <br>to information passed to Crimestoppers on cannabis cultivation increasing 28 <br>% in the month following the launch, which led to the dismantlement of <br>cannabis farms and a number of arrests across the country.</p><p> </p>","Lewes","Norman Baker",,"2014-07-17T14:17:34.5180658Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76850/answer","Biography information for Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76850/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76850/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-09","Cannabis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps her Department is taking to reduce the number of cannabis factories across the UK.","false","Biography information for David Simpson","Upper Bann","David Simpson","204714"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76851","Home Office","false","2014-07-21","<p> </p><p>Cambridge English are operating nine language test centres across Ukraine. The Home Office is working with Cambridge English to monitor access to these test centres.</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-07-21T14:10:56.3789864Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76851/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76851/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76851/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-09","Immigration: Ukraine","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will review the availability of language test centres in Ukraine in response to the current security situation in parts of that country.","false","Biography information for Mark Lazarowicz","Edinburgh North and Leith","Mark Lazarowicz","204792"
