"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76337","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-07-16","<p> </p><p>The table below shows losses of official equipment in core Defra for calendar years 2013 and 2014.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>2014*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Laptops</p></td><td><p>14</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Blackberrys</p></td><td><p>6</p></td><td><p>5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Mobile phones</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>* 1 January to 8 July 2014</p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-07-16T16:47:47.0241061Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76337/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76337/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76337/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-07-08","ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many mobile telephones, BlackBerrys and laptops were lost by his Department in (a) 2013 and (b) 2014 to date.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Bradshaw","Exeter","Mr Ben Bradshaw","204471"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76338","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-07-15","<p> </p><p>Beavers have not been an established part of our wildlife for the last 500 years. Before allowing them to be reintroduced into any location, their impact on a landscape that has changed considerably since they were last present should be assessed. Additionally the UK is currently free from the zoonotic disease <em>Echinocussus multilocularis</em>, a disease which some beavers are believed to host. To be sure that the country's disease free status is not compromised it is necessary to capture and test the animals. However, all decisions will be made with the welfare of the beavers in mind. There are no plans to kill the animals and a site suitable for the animals to be re-homed at is being actively sought.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","204413","2014-07-15T10:39:06.4597625Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76338/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76338/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76338/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-07-08","Beavers: Devon","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 26 June 2014, Official Report, column 330W, on beavers: Devon, for what reasons he plans to recapture and rehome the wild beavers in Devon; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","204414"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76339","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-07-15","<p> </p><p>Beavers have not been an established part of our wildlife for the last 500 years. Before allowing them to be reintroduced into any location, their impact on a landscape that has changed considerably since they were last present should be assessed. Additionally the UK is currently free from the zoonotic disease <em>Echinocussus multilocularis</em>, a disease which some beavers are believed to host. To be sure that the country's disease free status is not compromised it is necessary to capture and test the animals. However, all decisions will be made with the welfare of the beavers in mind. There are no plans to kill the animals and a site suitable for the animals to be re-homed at is being actively sought.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","204414","2014-07-15T10:39:06.725406Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76339/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76339/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76339/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-07-08","Beavers: Devon","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 26 June 2014, Official Report, column 330W, on beavers: Devon, what other options have been discussed by his Department, Natural England and the Animal Health and Veterinary Laboratories Agency apart from recapturing and rehoming the population of wild beavers in Devon.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","204413"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76340","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-07-14","<p> </p><p>The 2013 Water Framework Directive (WFD) classification results for England report that 1,017 rivers are assessed as being of, or having potential for, good ecological status. This is 21% of assessed river water bodies. These are the most recent classification results available for Cycle 1 of the WFD planning cycle (2009 to 2015).</p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-07-14T11:20:39.3239518Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76340/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76340/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76340/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-07-08","Rivers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many English rivers he assesses are of good ecological status.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","204542"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76341","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-07-14","<p> </p><p>The specific year-by-year statistics requested are not routinely calculated for marine protected areas; 9.4% of the UK's seas are currently designated as marine protected areas.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2014-07-14T11:25:40.8987989Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76341/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76341/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76341/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-07-08","Marine Protected Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what proportion of the total land mass of the UK was classified as a marine protected area or a marine conservation area in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","204634"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76342","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-07-14","<p> </p><p>There will be three trial Digital Support Centres (DSCs) for specific invited applicants to test the service which will be run over the summer. These will be based in Cumbria and in Devon. Further DSCs will become available in the autumn to support farmers across England as more farmers from other areas are invited to register. The RPA is working now to identify the most appropriate locations for the DSCs to support this staged roll out. This analysis will include likely demand alongside information we have on Broadband not-spots and areas where trusted intermediaries are operating. It is anticipated that there will be more than 10 DSCs available as demand grows.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2014-07-14T11:52:06.8776691Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76342/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76342/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76342/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-07-08","Common Agricultural Policy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, pursuant to the contribution of the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs of 7 July 2014, Official Report, columns 127-31, on Common Agricultural Policy, where the 10 centres for digital assistance for farmers will be located.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","204672"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76343","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-14","<p>We regularly raise the blasphemy laws and their misuse against those of all faiths at the highest levels in Pakistan. During the visit of Pakistan Prime Minister Sharif in April, the Prime Minister, my Right Hon. Friend the Member for Witney (Mr Cameron), raised our concerns as well as the need for reforms. We will continue to press the Pakistani government to make progress in this area.</p>","Faversham and Mid Kent","Hugh Robertson",,"2014-07-14T11:29:54.5098127Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76343/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugh Robertson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76343/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76343/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-08","Pakistan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent steps he has taken to encourage the repeal of blasphemy laws in Pakistan.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Mr Nigel Dodds","204618"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76344","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-14","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office has not had discussions with the European Commission's Radicalisation Awareness Network (RAN) and its working group on Voices of Victims of Terrorism in the last three years, but did send a representative to a RAN working group meeting in 2013 on a separate issue.</p>","Faversham and Mid Kent","Hugh Robertson",,"2014-07-14T11:33:38.0802212Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76344/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugh Robertson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76344/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76344/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-08","Terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions his Department has had with the European Commission's Radicalisation Awareness Network and its Working Group on Voices of Victims of Terrorism in the last three years.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Mr Nigel Dodds","204620"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76345","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-14","<p>Promoting and protecting the freedom of religion or belief is a priority for UK foreign policy. We pursue it in our bilateral work and lobbying of other Governments, and through our human rights programme funding. We have also stepped up training in the Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) on the influence of faith, in many parts of the world, on governments, communities and individuals.</p><p>Our work is based on the full definition of freedom of religion or belief as set out in article 18 the Universal Declaration of Human Rights. This includes the right to manifest your faith, either alone or in community with others and in public or private, through teaching, practice, worship and observance.</p><p>The FCO Minister responsible for freedom of religion or belief, the Senior Minister of State, my noble Friend the right hon. Baroness Warsi, has convened meetings of international leaders to generate support for practical steps to promote freedom of religion or belief and to fight religious intolerance. At the Global Summit to End Sexual Violence in Conflict, Baroness Warsi chaired a dialogue between political and faith leaders, and supported a separate non-governmental organization (NGO)-led event, to explore the role faith groups play, and to enlist their support for the objectives of the summit.</p><p>Freedoms of association and peaceful assembly, enshrined in both the Universal Declaration and the International Covenant on Civil and Political Rights, are fundamental for democratic societies, where people must be able to gather (formally or informally), to express themselves, and to have a meaningful say in issues that affect them. Though these rights are not among the FCO's six thematic human rights priorities, they feature prominently in our dialogue with individual countries and in international fora about governance, the rule of law and human rights in general.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2014-07-14T15:07:27.5051335Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76345/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76345/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76345/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-08","Religious Freedom","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps he is taking to emphasise adherence to fundamental freedoms of religion and association as part of the UK's foreign policy.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Mr Nigel Dodds","204616"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76346","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-14","<p>On 3 July, the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my right hon. Friend the Member for Richmond (Yorks) (Mr Hague) discussed the political situation in Israel and the Occupied Palestinian Territories with the Israeli Foreign Minister.</p>","Faversham and Mid Kent","Hugh Robertson",,"2014-07-14T08:05:04.9664534Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76346/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugh Robertson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76346/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76346/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-08","Middle East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, when he last met his Israeli counterpart to discuss the political situation in Israel and Palestine; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Iain McKenzie","Inverclyde","Iain McKenzie","204601"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76347","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-14","<p>We remain committed to supporting the Zimbabwean people in achieving a prosperous and democratic future, including through engagement with the Government of Zimbabwe. The UK continues to hold regular high-level meetings with the government and others across the political spectrum to promote democracy and good governance and discuss a range of issues.</p>","Boston and Skegness","Mark Simmonds",,"2014-07-14T17:21:31.8956307Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76347/answer","Biography information for Mark Simmonds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76347/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76347/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-08","Zimbabwe","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made relations with the government of Zimbabwe; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Ms Diane Abbott","Hackney North and Stoke Newington","Ms Diane Abbott","204528"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76348","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-14","<p>We have not deployed a Team of Experts (ToE) to Burma to date, but are currently considering ways in which a ToE or other international or local actors might best assist in the delivery of PSVI objectives in Burma. We continue to lobby the Burmese Government on the prevention of sexual violence in conflict, and to support projects in Burma to that end. Most recently in June, I discussed this issue with Deputy Foreign Minister U Thant Kyaw at the Global Summit to End Sexual Violence in Conflict.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire","204480","2014-07-14T08:49:34.4869076Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76348/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76348/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76348/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-08","Burma","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what work has been done by experts from the Preventing Sexual Violence Initiative on the reported use of sexual violence by the military in Burma.","false","Biography information for Fiona O'Donnell","East Lothian","Fiona O'Donnell","204537"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76349","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-14","<p>Human rights continue to be an integral part of our dialogue and relationship with Colombia. The Embassy continues to publicly support human rights work. I raised human rights with the Colombian government during my visit to Colombia last month. This followed visits by both the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my right hon. Friend the Member for Richmond (Yorks) (Mr Hague) and the Deputy Prime Minister, my right hon. Friend the Member for Sheffield, Hallam (Mr Clegg), who each raised the issue of human rights with President Santos in February.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2014-07-14T11:02:59.9256309Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76349/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76349/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76349/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-08","Colombia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will make representations to his Colombian counterpart drawing his attention to public support for human rights activists in Colombia.","false","Biography information for Robert Flello","Stoke-on-Trent South","Robert Flello","204546"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76350","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-14","<p>The UK continues to work closely with the Colombian government on the implementation of the UN Guiding Principles on Business and Human Rights, in line with our commitment to working for widespread international uptake.</p><p>British Embassy officials in Bogota have met with the government, civil society and business in Colombia on various occasions to discuss the UK Action plan on business and human rights. Last year, the Foreign and Commonwealth Office funded a project to assist Colombia in drafting its own national policy on Human Rights. This contributed to the Colombian public policy on Business and Human Rights which has been formed as a result of consulattion across 33 regions and involving over 19,000 people.</p><p> </p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2014-07-14T11:16:42.8367912Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76350/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76350/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76350/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-08","Colombia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will make representations to his Colombian counterpart about ensuring that British businesses and investors do not buy illegally obtained Colombian land before it is restored to its rightful owners.","false","Biography information for Robert Flello","Stoke-on-Trent South","Robert Flello","204547"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76351","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-14","<p>The British Embassy in Bogota receives regular reporting on the security and human rights situation in Colombia from a range of sources. This includes allegations of links between paramilitaries and the public forces but not information on the prevalence of the problem.</p><p>President Santos' government is making a genuine effort to improve respect for human rights in Colombia. Since 2008 the Colombian armed forces have introduced a widespread programme to promote respect for human rights. The UN has helped the Colombian Ministry of Defence to introduce reforms in the army for the last five years and all soldiers receive mandatory training on human rights.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2014-07-14T14:57:48.8420461Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76351/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76351/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76351/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-08","Colombia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what reports he has received on the prevalence of Colombian paramilitary involvement with the police and the armed forces of that country.","false","Biography information for Robert Flello","Stoke-on-Trent South","Robert Flello","204552"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76352","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-14","<p>During my recent visit to Colombia from 25 to 27 June, I met two Deputy Ministers for Foreign Affairs and heads of the Colombian government's major human rights agencies. This included the National Protection Unit. I raised the safety of Colombian land restitution claimants. Prior to, and during my visit, I was briefed on this issue by leading international and Colombian non-governmental organisations (NGOs).</p><p>Whilst security for claimants and those returning to their land remains a key concern, our 2013 Human Rights Report (released on 10 April 2014) notes that progress has been made on the issue of land restitution. Between 1 January 2012 and 31 December 2013, over 200,000 victims received reparations under the Victims and Land Restitution law. By the end of 2013, there were 54,063 registered land restitution claims.</p><p> </p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2014-07-14T11:20:35.3585192Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76352/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76352/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76352/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-08","Colombia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will make representations to his Colombian counterpart about guarantees for the safety of Colombian land restitution claimants.","false","Biography information for Robert Flello","Stoke-on-Trent South","Robert Flello","204550"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76353","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-14","<p> </p><p>The stability of the North African region is important to the UK. Extremist groups threaten regional security and the interests of our nation and our allies. The British Government has an ongoing dialogue with the United States on counter-terrorism issues, including on Northern Africa.</p><p> </p>","Faversham and Mid Kent","Hugh Robertson",,"2014-07-14T11:28:15.5052331Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76353/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugh Robertson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76353/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76353/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-08","North Africa","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with his US counterpart on tackling the threat from Islamic extremism in northern Africa.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","204392"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76354","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-14","<p>Since the formation of the All Progressive Congress in 2013, I have met Governor Fashola (Lagos State), Governor Amaechi (Rivers State) and Governor Shettima (Borno State). I am unaware of any other meetings between the Foreign Secretary or other FCO Ministers and leading members of the All Progressive Congress.</p><p>We stand ready to work with the Nigerian government and politicians of all parties to uphold the democratic process in Nigeria and ensure the elections in 2015 are as free, fair and peaceful as possible.</p>","Boston and Skegness","Mark Simmonds",,"2014-07-14T17:15:18.447057Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76354/answer","Biography information for Mark Simmonds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76354/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76354/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-08","Nigeria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions (a) he and (b) other Ministers in his Department have had with leading members of the Nigerian opposition party, the All Progressive Congress; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","204401"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76355","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-14","<p>We have no plans at present to commission an inquiry into the international support network for Boko Haram in Nigeria and Cameroon. However, we are working with international partners, including Nigeria and its neighbours, the US and France to share information and coordinate efforts to defeat Boko Haram, including through the creation of a Regional Intelligence Fusion Unit (RIFU).</p>","Boston and Skegness","Mark Simmonds",,"2014-07-14T17:19:43.2534451Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76355/answer","Biography information for Mark Simmonds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76355/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76355/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-08","Nigeria and Cameroon","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will commission an inquiry into the international support network for Boko Haram in Nigeria and Cameroon; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","204402"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76356","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-14","<p>Consular assistance for British nationals in Bhutan is provided from British Deputy High Commission based in Kolkata. We encourage all travellers to Bhutan to check our travel advice before travelling.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2014-07-14T15:20:25.1057422Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76356/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76356/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76356/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-08","Bhutan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what consular assistance his Department offers to British nationals travelling in Bhutan.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","204378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76357","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-15","<p>The UK is playing a leading role in helping Nigeria to tackle the terrorist threat from Boko Haram and related group Ansaru, working closely both with the Nigerian authorities and international partners. The UK proscribed Boko Haram in July 2013.</p><p>Following the abduction in April of the Chibok schoolgirls the Prime Minister offered a package of support including: tactical advice and training for the military to help counter terrorism; military air surveillance capacity and intelligence support to help try to locate the girls; £1 million towards the UN Safe Schools initiative. The Foreign Secretary hosted a Ministerial meeting on security in Nigeria on 12 June in London. The meeting delivered agreements from Nigeria, neighbouring countries and international partners on improved security, intelligence cooperation, and commitment both to coordination of development work in the region and to empowerment and education of women.</p><p>We are also working with Nigeria on a range of judicial and security projects to improve military capacity, policing, access to justice and prosecution of terrorists. All UK counter terrorism work is subject to the Overseas Security and Justice Assistance (OSJA) process.</p>","Boston and Skegness","Mark Simmonds",,"2014-07-15T09:22:08.5607685Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76357/answer","Biography information for Mark Simmonds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76357/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76357/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-08","Nigeria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what support his Department plans to offer to Nigeria in tackling the threat of Boko Haram.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","204388"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76358","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-14","<p>We believe there have been links between Boko Haram and AQIM (Al Qaeda in the Islamic Maghreb). Boko Haram's off-shoot Ansaru is also believe to have had connections. However, we assess that Boko Haram's main motivation remains the end of democratic government and creation of an Islamic State in Nigeria.</p>","Boston and Skegness","Mark Simmonds",,"2014-07-14T16:29:48.0192449Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76358/answer","Biography information for Mark Simmonds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76358/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76358/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-08","Africa","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of links between Boko Haram and other Islamic extremist groups in Africa.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","204389"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76359","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-14","<p>We welcome all efforts by Cameroon and Nigeria to strengthen their security cooperation to defeat Boko Haram.</p><p>I discussed Cameroon's efforts to tackle Boko Haram with the Cameroonian Prime Minister and Foreign Minister when I visited Yaoundé in May. Both signalled their willingness to work with partners to combat Boko Haram. On 12 June in London, the Cameroonian Foreign Minister attended a Ministerial meeting on security in Nigeria, hosted by the Foreign Secretary. A key outcome was regional agreement to increased levels of coordinated border patrols by Nigeria and its neighbours including Cameroon.</p>","Boston and Skegness","Mark Simmonds",,"2014-07-14T16:34:38.437086Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76359/answer","Biography information for Mark Simmonds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76359/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76359/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-08","Nigeria and Cameroon","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will discuss with his counterpart in Cameroon the need for constructive dialogue between that country and Nigeria in tackling Boko Haram; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","204390"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76360","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-15","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) takes its responsibilities for protecting information assets seriously and complies with all the mandatory requirements of the Security Policy Framework. As such, it has in place, security incident management procedures to ensure losses are dealt with appropriately.<br> <br>The FCO's central records show the following equipment reported as lost or stolen, overseas and in the UK in (a) 2013 and (b) 2014 until 30 June:</p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td colspan="2">Lost/Stolen 2013</td><td colspan="2">Lost/Stolen 2014</td></tr><tr><td>Items</td><td>UK</td><td>Overseas</td><td>UK</td><td>Overseas</td></tr><tr><td>BlackBerrys</td><td>24</td><td>31</td><td>3</td><td>22</td></tr><tr><td>Laptops</td><td>5</td><td>7</td><td>3</td><td>1</td></tr></tbody></table><p>Blackberry devices are protected with remote wipe when the device is reported lost or stolen. In addition, after five failed attempts to access the password, the auto-wipe will clear the device of any data.</p><p>Information on the number of mobile telephones lost or stolen is not held centrally and can be obtained only at disproportionate cost. To enable maximum value for money, mobile phones are controlled by individual Posts where they take advantage of local telephone rates and mobile telephone deals. Hence there is no central management or monitoring of mobile usage.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2014-07-15T16:31:59.2719353Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76360/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76360/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76360/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-08","ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many mobile telephones, BlackBerrys and laptops were lost by his Department in (a) 2013 and (b) 2014 to date.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Bradshaw","Exeter","Mr Ben Bradshaw","204472"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76361","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-15","<p>a) With regard to Albania, our positive bilateral relations means the UK is seen by Albania as partner of choice across a number of reform areas, which frequently results in commercial contracts for UK businesses. Crown Agents' contract to reform the customs administration is a good example of this. More broadly, our Embassy advises and assists UK businesses who are interested in investing or operating in Albania, and is active in promoting opportunities.</p><p>For example, our Embassy has provided advice to British companies in the telecommunications, oil and gas, mining, pipeline, flight training, pharmaceutical, travel, engineering, and consultancy sectors. In addition our Embassy maintains good relationships with local foreign investor associations to whom referrals for advice are made.</p><p>b) The Foreign and Commonweath Office (FCO) is active in promoting the UK's trading relationship with Montenegro through FCO-funded projects that help create an environment in which strong economic relations can thrive. These include projects aimed at: strengthening Montenegro's rule of law framework; fighting corruption; tackling tax fraud; and increasing transparency. Additionally, our Embassy in Montenegro facilitates cooperation between UK businesses and their Montenegrin counterparts. A recent example of successful trade relations between businesses from the two countries is Porto Montenegro – a sea-front development in Tivat worth more than €180 million, in which more than 50 British companies were involved.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2014-07-15T15:10:37.5718614Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76361/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76361/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76361/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-08","Balkans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps his Department has taken to strengthen trading relations between the UK and (a) Albania and (b) Montenegro.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","204379"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76362","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-15","<p>The Prime Minister, my right hon. Friend the Member for Witney (Mr Cameron) issued a statement on 30 June, following the discovery of the missing Israeli teenagers saying that his prayers and thoughts were with the families of the teenagers. Our Ambassador to Israel, Matthew Gould, attended the funeral.</p><p>The Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my right hon. Friend the Member for Richmond (Yorks) (Mr Hague) expressed his deepest sympathies to the families and to all Israelis as they mourned this sad loss.</p><p> </p>","Boston and Skegness","Mark Simmonds",,"2014-07-15T13:17:38.2000846Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76362/answer","Biography information for Mark Simmonds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76362/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76362/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-08","Israel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what condolences the UK has offered to Israel following the discovery of the bodies of the three murdered teenagers, Naftali Freikel, Gilad Sha'ar and Eyal Yifrah.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","204384"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76363","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-14","<p>Our objective is to see a prosperous and stable Iraq as part of a stable region. The advance by the Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant (ISIL) in Iraq in June threatens this. Reported atrocities of summary executions, sexual violence and attacks against religious buildings by ISIL all go to show the importance of taking a strong stand against the extremists. In the immediate term the UK has provided £5 million of humanitarian aid to alleviate the suffering of those affected by recent violence. During his recent visit to Iraq, the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my Right Hon. Friend the Member for Richmond (Yorks) (Mr Hague) emphasised the importance of unity and political inclusion to make an effective security response possible.</p>","Faversham and Mid Kent","Hugh Robertson",,"2014-07-14T11:32:01.5345916Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76363/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugh Robertson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76363/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76363/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-08","Iraq","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the implications for his policies of the rise of Islamic terrorism in Northern Iraq.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","204386"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76364","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-14","<p>Terrorist attacks in Nigeria have caused great suffering in communities of different faiths and ethnicities. Boko Haram cannot be seen simply as a result of Christian-Muslim tensions and their attacks are often indiscriminate.</p><p>The British Government is committed to working with the Nigerian authorities to tackle security problems in Nigeria. We recognise the underlying issues of poverty and inequality, which lead to inter-communal tensions and conflict in Nigeria and we urge political, traditional and religious leaders to work together in order to resolve these issues. DFID are delivering a range of programmes in six of the northern Nigerian states designed to address the drivers of violent extremism and conflict.</p>","Boston and Skegness","Mark Simmonds",,"2014-07-14T16:26:21.1562235Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76364/answer","Biography information for Mark Simmonds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76364/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76364/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-08","Nigeria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the rise in Islamic terrorism in Nigeria.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","204387"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76365","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-11","<p>Our Embassy in Sarajevo assists UK companies wishing to do business in Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) by supporting them through the full range of UK Trade and Investment (UKTI) services. The UKTI offer includes identifying and publicising business opportunities, offering expert local market advice, and facilitating access to information, contacts and partners which would not otherwise be accessible.</p><p>UK companies in BiH focus predominantly on roads and related infrastructure, energy, mining and aid-funded business. The UKTI office in the Embassy helps UK companies to exploit particular opportunities in these areas, and has established a strong network of contacts which assist UK business.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2014-07-11T14:30:06.2594662Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76365/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76365/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76365/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-08","Bosnia and Herzegovina","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps his Department has taken to strengthen trading relations between the UK and Bosnia and Herzegovina.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","204397"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76366","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-11","<p>Foreign and Commonwealth Office travel advice provides objective information and advice to help British nationals make better-informed decisions about foreign travel. This includes information on security. Our travel advice is reviewed regularly, and is updated if we are aware of an incident that might significantly affect Britons travelling or living in the area. The current travel advice for Ukraine is on the gov.uk website at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/foreign-travel-advice/ukraine" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/foreign-travel-advice/ukraine</a>.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2014-07-11T14:25:15.3522295Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76366/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76366/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76366/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-08","Ukraine","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what security guidance his Department provides to British nationals wishing to travel to Ukraine.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","204396"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76367","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-14","<p>If Mr Hall needs to use his passport to travel overseas it is possible for him/his lawyer to apply to the court for “international bail” which, if agreed, would enable Mr Hall's lawyer to retrieve his passport for him to use, subject to any conditions that the court might set.</p><p>If Mr Hall does not wish to apply for international bail and wishes to apply for a replacement passport instead, we must first of all make a formal request to the court for the return of his original passport. If we do not receive Mr Hall's passport, or a response from the authorities, within ten days, we would discuss with Mr Hall his options for obtaining a replacement passport. However, an approach by the Embassy to the Court in this way might result in Mr Hall's bail being revoked. If Mr Hall asked us to do this, we would request that he sign a pro-forma acknowledging that the consequences of applying for a new passport have been explained to him. We have also asked Mr Hall to bear in mind that the Courts may have placed some sort of immigration stop/block against his name/passport number (or might do so upon receipt of a letter from the Embassy asking for the return of his passport), and so even if Mr Hall did get his current passport back, or obtain a new passport, he may not be able to leave Thailand on it. Mr Hall has also been advised to consult his lawyer about these issues.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2014-07-14T10:56:48.3084889Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76367/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76367/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76367/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-08","Thailand","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps HM Embassy in Bangkok is taking to retrieve the passport of Andy Hall.","false","Biography information for Mr David Ward","Bradford East","Mr David Ward","204441"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76368","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-14","<p>I have not had any discussions with my Thai counterpart on the allegations of mistreatment of elephants in trekking camps in Thailand. However, my noble friend Lord de Mauley, Parliamentary Under Secretary of State at DEFRA, visited Bangkok at the beginning of May 2014 and was able to pursue a number of animal welfare issues with the Thai government. He discussed efforts to counter the illegal trade in wildlife in Thailand with his Thai counterpart, senior officials, non-government organisations (NGOs), the UN and like-minded Embassies.</p><p>Additionally, our Embassy in Bangkok has reinforced the messages stemming from the February 2014 London Declaration to prevent illegal wildlife trade, and continues to engage with those organisations in Thailand which are working to deliver this agenda despite the coup.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2014-07-14T15:06:07.0718518Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76368/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76368/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76368/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-08","Thailand","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with his Thai counterpart on allegations of the mistreatment of elephants in trekking camps in Thailand.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","204394"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76369","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-10","<p>We are unable to provide direct consular assistance in Somalia. However, while we advise against all travel to Somalia except for the cities of Hargeisa and Berbera, to which we advise against all but essential travel, we have provided some consular assistance to British nationals who have travelled to Somalia through our embassy in Addis Ababa and High Commission in Nairobi. There have been three cases so far in this financial year. There were seventeen cases in 2013-14, eight in 2012-13, nine in 2011-12, and ten in 2010-11.</p>","Boston and Skegness","Mark Simmonds",,"2014-07-10T16:16:17.7273238Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76369/answer","Biography information for Mark Simmonds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76369/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76369/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-08","Somalia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many British nationals have required emergency consular assistance in Somalia in each of the last four years.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","204395"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76370","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-14","<p>We have not deployed a Team of Experts (ToE) to Burma to date, but are currently considering ways in which a ToE or other international or local actors might best assist in the delivery of PSVI objectives in Burma. We continue to lobby the Burmese Government on the prevention of sexual violence in conflict, and to support projects in Burma to that end. Most recently in June, I discussed this issue with Deputy Foreign Minister U Thant Kyaw at the Global Summit to End Sexual Violence in Conflict.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire","204537","2014-07-14T08:49:34.3775168Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76370/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76370/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76370/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-08","Burma","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether experts from the Preventing Sexual Violence Initiative have been sent to Burma to investigate the attempted rape of an ethnic Chin woman by a soldier from the Burmese Army.","false","Biography information for Fiona O'Donnell","East Lothian","Fiona O'Donnell","204480"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76371","Department of Health","false","2014-07-14","<p>Senior officials in the Department and Her Majesty's Treasury have discussed the business case for meningococcal B immunisation.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-07-14T10:03:14.4689098Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76371/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76371/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76371/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-08","Meningitis: Vaccination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what discussions he has had with the Chancellor of the Exchequer on the approval of his Department's business case for the meningococcal B vaccine.","false","Biography information for Sir Tony Cunningham","Workington","Sir Tony Cunningham","204486"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76372","Department of Health","false","2014-07-14","<p>The Department allocates budgets including, for the School Fruit and Vegetable Scheme on the basis of financial years (beginning in April) rather than academic years (beginning in September). The Department has not yet set its central budgets, which include the School Fruit and Vegetable Scheme, for the 2015-16 financial year which covers the first seven months of the 2015-16 academic year. The remaining five months of the 2015-16 academic year fall into the 2016-17 financial year which will be subject to the next Spending Review.</p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-07-14T13:01:34.3200957Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76372/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76372/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76372/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-08","School Fruit and Vegetable Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how much his Department has allocated to the School Fruit and Vegetable scheme for the 2015-16 school year.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Mr Frank Field","204446"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76373","Department of Health","false","2014-07-15","<p>The Government consistently recognises the contribution that charities make to the mental health of the people of this country. As recognised in our mental health strategy, <em>No health without mental health</em> and in <em>Closing the Gap: Priorities of essential change in mental health, </em>charities are integral partners to our drive to improve the mental health and wellbeing of the nation.</p><p> </p><p>The Voluntary Sector Strategic Partner Programme brings together a range of voluntary sector organisations to inform and shape national policy. The programme provides a forum for policy makers to reach hundreds of thousands of voluntary and community sector organisations through the extensive depth and reach of the partners' networks. The Programme includes a number of mental health charities including the Depression Alliance, the leading charity in the United Kingdom for anyone affected by depression. The Depression Alliance is a member of the Mental Health Providers Forum, who represents a number of charities on the Voluntary Sector Strategic Partner Programme.</p><p> </p><p>The <em>Time to Change</em> campaign, led by Mind and Rethink Mental Illness, seeks to end discrimination against people with mental health problems, including those with depression. Between 2011 and 2015 the Department is providing £16 million to the campaign. <em>Time to Change</em> includes a national high-profile marketing and media campaign which has successfully reached 29 million people. Recent research has shown a reduction in the average levels of discrimination since 2008.</p><p> </p><p>The Department, alongside Public Health England and NHS England, is working with voluntary sector stakeholders through the Health and Care Voluntary Sector Strategic Partner Programme, including the Mental Health Consortia, to support voluntary sector organisations in health and social care and help them realise their potential.</p><p> </p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb",,"2014-07-15T13:53:30.6026649Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76373/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76373/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76373/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-08","Depressive Illnesses: Charities","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent steps his Department has taken to raise awareness of charities set up to help people suffering from depression.","false","Biography information for David Simpson","Upper Bann","David Simpson","204491"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76374","Department of Health","false","2014-07-15","<p>I refer my Rt. hon. Friend to the answer that I gave him on 8 July 2014, <em>Official Report</em>, column 237W.</p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb",,"2014-07-15T14:23:14.878205Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76374/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76374/answer","PQ204436 - Hansard Extract.docx","PQ204436 - Hansard Extract.docx","Hansard Extract","Hansard Extract","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76374/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-08","Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 26 June 2014, Official Report, column 281W, on medical treatments, what the most plausible cost per quality adjusted life-year was for each technology appraisal conducted by the National Institute for Care Excellence since June 2010; what the estimated patient population was for each appraised indication; on which appraisals the end-of-life criteria were applied in each final appraisal determination; and on what dates each appraisal was (a) initiated and (b) concluded.","false","Biography information for Mr Stephen O'Brien","Eddisbury","Mr Stephen O'Brien","204436"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76375","Department of Health","false","2014-07-15","<p>The total Department spend on national anti-smoking campaigns (Smokefree) over the last four years is as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial Year</p></td><td><p>Media Spend £ million</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>0.46</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>3.16</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>8.21</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>7.64</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>It should be noted that the figures for 2013-14 are provisional.</p><p> </p><p>For spend before April 2012, advertising spend is defined as covering only media spend (inclusive of agency commissions but excluding production costs, Central Office of Information (COI) commission and VAT). All figures exclude advertising rebates and audit adjustments and therefore may differ from COI official turnover figures. All figures are rounded to the nearest £10,000. These figures do not include the Department's recruitment/classified advertising costs and ad hoc spend under £10,000. These figures may include occasional minor spend through COI by National Health Service organisations, to supplement national campaigns in their area. While this expenditure has been excluded as far as possible so that this reflects central departmental spend, it would incur disproportionate cost to validate that every item of NHS expenditure has been removed.</p><p>From April 2012 onward is Departmental advertising spend only. Spend from April 2013 onwards is Public Health England advertising spend only. Advertising spend is defined as covering only media spend (inclusive of agency commissions but excluding production costs and VAT). All figures are rounded to the nearest £10,000.</p><p> </p><p>Further information on the harms of smoking can be found on the Smokefree website at</p><p> </p><p>www.nhs.uk/smokefree</p><p> </p><p>and also in the range of Smokefree support products.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-07-15T15:36:45.091452Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76375/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76375/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/76375/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-08","Smoking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what his Department has spent on anti-smoking awareness campaigns in each of the last four years.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","204385"
